**Scoring rationale (delta from `.harness/spec.md` baseline of 35):**

| LP | Old | New | Reason |
|----|-----|-----|--------|
| 5 Feedback Loops | 3 | **4** | SSE streaming now implemented in `dashboard/app/api/analyze/route.ts`; `phase_update` events give structured pass/fail per phase — genuine improvement over raw WebSocket text |
| 8 Quality Gating | 2 | **3** | `dashboard/app/api/analyze/route.ts` Phase 3 runs `tier-evaluator + agentic-review` as a discrete phase with scored JSON output; partial gating now exists even though no second-pass evaluator tier runs post-build in the backend |

All other scores hold from the spec.md baseline. **Total: 36/60 → ZTE Level 2 (Autonomous band, lower bound).**

The system crossed the Autonomous threshold (36) solely due to the dashboard's structured SSE phase feedback loop and the evaluator phase in the 8-phase pipeline — but it is one regression away from dropping back to Assisted. The five weakest points (Error Recovery 2, Session Continuity 2, Trigger Automation 2, Knowledge Retention 2, Workflow Standardization 2) all remain at floor value and represent the highest-ROI improvement surface.